\bf Hint:
e^{\theta i}=cos\theta+isin\theta
e^{ \frac{\pi}{3} i } + e^{ -\frac{\pi}{3} i }=(\cos(\tfrac{\pi}{3})+i\sin(\tfrac{\pi}{3}))+(\cos(-\tfrac{\pi}{3})+i\sin(-\tfrac{\pi}{3}))=
(\tfrac{1}{2}+i\tfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2})+(\tfrac{1}{2}-i\tfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2})=\tfrac{1}{2}+\tfrac{1}{2}=1
